Since [Firefox 3](http://getfirefox.com/) is now official, I've made Webconverger 3 official.

So [[burn_webc-3.0.mini.iso_to_a_CD|iso]] to effectively try Firefox or rather the brand-free [Iceweasel](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iceweasel) 3 in a safe **live** environment.

I actually prefer the LiveUSB version. [Download](http://download.webconverger.com/) webc-3.0.mini.img and checkout the [[instructions_for_putting_Webconverger_on_your_USB_stick|usb]]. Boots in a minute on my Thinkpad X40!

There probably will be some [[bugs|blog/entry/Bugs]] so please report them to the [mailing list / forum](http://groups.google.com/group/webc-users/topics) or directly to me if you so wish. For the more technically inclined, see [Iceweasel bugs](http://bugs.debian.org/src:iceweasel) and [Mozilla's BTS](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/).

Enjoy and congratulations to [Mozilla](http://www.mozilla.org/) on the historic bit of PR which is [download day](http://blog.mozilla.com/blog/2008/06/18/over-8-million-way-to-go/).
